  "text": "14, [CITATION_1] The quantum defect results in a heat load of approximately 6 %, which corresponds to a quantum defect induced heat load of 6% · 190 W ≈ 10 W for a FOA with 10 W seed and 13 dB gain. In this case, a photodarkening induced heat load of 10 W will double the heat load but only affect the optical efficiency slightly with a reduction in gain of <0.5 dB.",
